A teenage girl is in a critical condition after she was knocked over by a bus on the R27 in Woodbridge Island, Milnerton in Cape Town. It is reported that the incident took place around 8:45am on Monday. Upon arrival, paramedics found the girl, believed to be 15 year’s old  trapped under the bus. According to the paramedics, the girl sustained serious injuries to her leg and head. She was transported to Groote Schuur Hospital for further medical care. Local authorities were on the scene for further investigations. -TNA Reporter